<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.512/165</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 774</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-19">May 19,
                                1942</date>.<lb/>[Received June 5.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                            Legation’s despatches no. 640 of February 24, 1942 and no. 658 [<hi rend="italic">656</hi>] of March 3, 1942, and to report that, in
                            accordance with the authorization contained in the Department’s telegram
                            no. 84 of March [<hi rend="italic">May</hi>] 4, 1942, 11 p.m., an <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi><note n="62" xml:id="d606fn62">See
                                draft of <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>, <ref target="#pg_490">p. 490</ref>.</note> was left with my Spanish colleague, copies
                            of which are enclosed, on the subject of the payment by American
                            citizens to the Customs of the so-called Auxiliary Social Relief
                            Tax.</p>
                        <p>When I presented the <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> to my Spanish
                            colleague, he expressed great satisfaction with its conciliatory
                            character.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Rives Childs</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>